[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    154[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    155[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    156[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSix-stage pipeline shape is correct.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Ingest the demographic update or new record, detect a candidate name-change event, evaluate the candidate against the existing identity record, persist the temporal-name update with audit and sensitivity metadata, propagate the linkage to dependent stores, react to events that supersede prior linkages maps cleanly to the operational reality. The trigger-source heterogeneity (registration update, payer eligibility refresh, vital-records feed, cross-organizational match refresh, document upload, patient-facing app connection, bulk historical-records reconciliation) is correctly handled by a single downstream pipeline with event-aware re-evaluation.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    157[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDetection-as-load-bearing-addition is correctly elevated.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's strongest single architectural primitive: "the temporal model needs an explicit detector because the addition of a new name to an existing identity is structurally different from a new record matching an existing identity. The detector handles both the direct case (an explicit assertion of a name change) and the indirect case (a high-demographic-match record arriving with a different name from the matched identity). The indirect case is the dominant operational path and is the one that institutions tend to under-invest in."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    158[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThreshold calibration is name-change-specific.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly elevates the separate-from-5.1 calibration ("Re-using the recipe 5.1 thresholds for name-change decisions produces either too many false-merges ... or too many missed name changes ... The right thresholds for name-change events are derived from a separate calibration set"). DIRECT and INDIRECT thresholds are separately specified; the calibration discipline is institutional rather than magic-number.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    159[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSensitivity classification at the prior-name level rather than the identity level.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "A patient may have multiple name changes over a lifetime, with different sensitivity classifications for each. A divorce that reverts to a maiden name may have no special sensitivity, while a subsequent legal name change associated with gender transition has explicit privacy preferences. The model carries the classification at the prior-name level, not at the identity level, because a single identity can have prior names with different sensitivity treatments." This is the right granularity.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    160[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mMatcher-versus-access-control-envelope split-of-concerns.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly elevates this to architectural primitive: "the matcher always knows the linkage between current and prior names; specific users may or may not see the prior name based on their role, the sensitivity classification, the access purpose, and the patient's preferences. Hiding the linkage from the system itself defeats the matcher's job; hiding the prior name from the user surface is a presentation-and-access-control concern. The two are distinct."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    161[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPatient-self-assertion as a valid but weaker source.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The matcher accepts patient-self-assertion as a name-change source but treats it differently from document-backed assertions, with explicit pending-state and document-eventually-arrives pathway support.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    162[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mReversibility as the architecture rather than as a feature.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "A name-change event can be wrong, and the architecture has to support cleanly retracting it. The temporal-name record carries an event history, not just a current state; superseding events update the computed view without losing the underlying history; downstream consumers receive invalidation events that allow them to refresh derived state."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    163[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mMulti-source invalidation pipeline.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Step 6's enumeration of invalidation sources (correction, reversal, identity merge, identity unmerge, sensitivity-class update, document-strength upgrade, cross-organizational match invalidation) is comprehensive and operationally complete. The multi-source design accommodates the recipe's recognition that name changes have a multi-decade lifecycle with multiple opportunities for the prior decision to require update.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    164[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mTransactWriteItems plus outbox pattern is specified in Step 4 pseudocode.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This is a positive structural improvement on the chapter pattern: 5.1, 5.2, 5.3, 5.4, 5.5 all had a HIGH finding (Finding A1 in those reviews) for sequential write-without-transactional-wrapping; recipes 5.6 and 5.7 specify the pattern in the pseudocode. The outbox-drainer flow at Step 4D is correctly referenced.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    165[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAppend-only event log with computed current state.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "The record is an append-only event in the identity's history; the current state is computed from the event log. This pattern lets the resolver re-derive the current state under any historical configuration (which is what the audit layer needs for forensic-reconstruction queries)." This is the right pattern for the multi-decade lifecycle the recipe targets.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    166[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mReference-data-version tracking on every name-change event.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's repeated framing that every name-change resolution references the matcher_config_version, the nickname-dictionary version, the surname-change-pattern-models version, and the transliteration-maps version active at decision time is the right discipline for forensic reconstruction across reference-data-update cycles.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    167[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCross-organizational propagation as a non-fully-solvable problem.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take correctly elevates this: "most institutions cannot fully solve this on their own. A name change recorded at organization A propagates to organization B only through one of three pathways: the patient updates her record at organization B in person, the cross-facility refresh path detects the discrepancy at query time, or the patient-mediated flow propagates the change through a personal-health-record app." Each pathway has its own latency and coverage gaps. The patient-mediated path as strategic investment is the right framing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    168[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mHistorical retrofit as project rather than feature.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "Standing up the longitudinal-matching pipeline involves a one-time backfill that re-evaluates years of historical records against whatever name-change evidence is available." The Honest Take's elevation of patient-portal-driven confirmation pathway and conservative thresholds during backfill is the right operational discipline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    169[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mConfiguration-as-data discipline.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe consistently treats matcher_config_version, reference-data versions, threshold values, and sensitivity-classification rules as versioned configuration rather than hardcoded constants. Name-change events reference the versions active at decision time.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    170[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mWhy-This-Isn't-Production-Ready section names ten gaps.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Patient-preference UI and consent capture, reference-data sourcing and maintenance, threshold calibration and approval governance, three review queues with sensitivity-aware tooling, information-blocking compliance posture, cross-organizational propagation policy, historical backfill plan and execution, vital-records integration where available, idempotency and retry semantics, cohort-stratified accuracy monitoring discipline, compliance and operational ownership. The breadth is appropriate for a Complex-tier recipe.[K
