[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    218[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mExpert:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Architecture (recipe-specific, dignity-compliance lifecycle)[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    219[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Honest Take's "would do differently the second time" paragraph: "invest in the access-control envelope as a versioned, queryable artifact from day one. The first version of the recipe will treat the envelope as a small bag of policy fields attached to each prior-name event. The second version will recognize that the envelope has its own lifecycle (patient-preference updates, jurisdictional-policy changes, sensitivity-class upgrades, audit-rule modifications) and needs versioning, history, and a query API. The envelope is consulted by chart-rendering, release-of-information, patient-portal, audit, and analytics consumers; treating it as an undifferentiated bag of fields produces ad-hoc display logic that is hard to govern. Build the envelope as a first-class concept from the beginning." Step 5's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mapply_sensitivity_and_consent_envelope[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m returns an envelope object that is attached to the prior-name event in Step 6's persistence; the envelope is treated as a per-event attribute rather than as a versioned artifact with its own lifecycle.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    220[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly elevates the access-control envelope to architectural primitive ("the matcher always knows the linkage; specific users may not know the linkage; that distinction is operationally meaningful and architecturally non-trivial") but the persistence layer treats it as a bag of policy fields attached to each prior-name event. The Honest Take's "would do differently" framing names the gap explicitly. Four concrete consequences of the bag-of-fields treatment, all of which are recipe-specific:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    221[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    222[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPatient-preference updates require event-level envelope rewrites.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A patient who updates her display preference from [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdefault[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m to [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mmasked[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m triggers an envelope update on every existing prior-name event for the same identity. Without a separate envelope-as-versioned-artifact concept, the rewrite has to fan out across every per-event envelope; race conditions between concurrent preference updates and ongoing matcher resolutions produce inconsistent envelope state.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    223[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    224[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mJurisdictional-policy changes require population-wide envelope rewrites.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A change in state law (post-Dobbs reproductive-health-care state law, post-Bostock employment-context implications) requires a population-wide envelope update. The bag-of-fields treatment requires walking every affected per-event envelope; the envelope-as-versioned-artifact treatment can promote a new policy version and have consumers query against it.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    225[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    226[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSensitivity-class upgrades need an explicit forward-only-disclosure-update framing.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly notes that "The architecture cannot retract disclosures that have already left the institution, but it can update the access-control envelope for future disclosures" but the bag-of-fields treatment makes this opaque: the patient-facing communication says "your envelope has been updated" without a clear reference to the envelope's history. The versioned-artifact treatment makes the history first-class and the patient-facing audit-summary-delivery feature can show the envelope-version timeline alongside the disclosure history.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    227[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    228[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m4[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAudit-rule modifications need their own lifecycle.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The audit rules within the envelope (every-disclosure-logged, every-query-logged, monthly-summary-to-patient-portal, etc.) may change independently of the sensitivity classification; the bag-of-fields treatment conflates the two. The versioned-artifact treatment lets audit rules evolve on their own cadence with their own governance.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    229[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    230[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Specify the access-control envelope as a versioned, queryable artifact in the persistence schema and the architecture pattern. Two write paths for envelope changes (the per-event envelope assignment from Step 5 produces a reference to a versioned envelope; envelope updates produce a new envelope version with a forward-only-disclosure-update framing). Three read paths for envelope consumers (chart-rendering reads the envelope-as-of-now for the requesting context; release-of-information reads the envelope-at-disclosure-time for the audit log; patient-portal-audit-summary-delivery reads the envelope-history for the time-window display). The envelope-versioning store is a separate DynamoDB table keyed on (envelope_id, version) with the current-version pointer in a GSI; consumers query by envelope_id and either consume the current version or a specified historical version. The envelope-update event flows through the same outbox-and-EventBridge-fan-out pattern as the name-change resolution, with the same access-control-aware routing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    231[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
