[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare appointment scheduling bot decomposes into eight logical stages: channel entry, input safety screening, intent classification, identity verification, conversational slot negotiation (search and refine), transactional fulfillment (hold, confirm, book), output safety screening, and audit logging. The cross-cutting concerns from the FAQ bot (knowledge-base curation, persona and prompt management, escalation, per-cohort monitoring) all carry forward; this recipe adds three new ones (tool-surface contract management, identity-assurance lifecycle, transactional-failure compensation).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CHANNEL ENTRY ─────────────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient connects through one of the configured         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    channels: web chat widget, in-app chat, SMS,           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    voice (with ASR/TTS), authenticated patient-portal     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    embed]                                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Greeting and disclosure]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identifies as a chatbot, not a human                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - States the bot's scope (scheduling, rescheduling,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      cancellation; not clinical)                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Offers an immediate path to a human                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Conversation session bootstrap]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generate session_id                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Capture channel, authentication context (if any),    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and any deep-link parameters (e.g., the patient      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      clicked a "schedule follow-up" link in their         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      after-visit summary)                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: session_id, channel, auth context]             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── INPUT SAFETY SCREENING ────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Same primitive as recipe 11.1, including:]             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis detection (preempts everything)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Prompt-injection detection                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - PHI minimization (before identity verification,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the bot does not need PHI; after identity            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      verification, the bot needs only what the            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      scheduling task requires)                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: input passes / input blocked-with-disposition] │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── INTENT CLASSIFICATION ─────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Map the user's request to one of the bot's intents]    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - new_appointment                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - reschedule_appointment                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - cancel_appointment                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - check_appointment                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - update_preferences                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - out_of_scope (defer to FAQ bot, to a human, or       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to the appropriate other handler)                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Out-of-scope handoff]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Clinical questions -> nurse triage                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Refill requests -> recipe 11.3 path                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Benefits-specific questions -> recipe 11.5 path      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - General FAQ -> recipe 11.1 path                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: in-scope intent | out-of-scope handoff]        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── IDENTITY VERIFICATION ─────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Verify the patient's identity at the assurance level   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    appropriate for the intent and the channel]            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Authenticated session path]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient is logged into the patient portal            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The session conveys an authenticated patient_id      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The bot accepts the patient_id as verified and       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      proceeds                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Unauthenticated channel path]                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient enters name, date of birth                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot asks for a confirmation factor (last four of     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the phone number on file, ZIP code on file, or       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      a one-time code sent to the phone or email on file)  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identity verification tool returns a match           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      confidence score and a verified patient_id           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Identity verification failures]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Below-threshold match -> "I'm having trouble         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      finding your record. Let me get you to someone       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      who can help."                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multiple matches -> request additional               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      disambiguating information                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - No match -> "I don't see a record matching that.     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      Are you a new patient? I can help you start the      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      new-patient process."                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Step-up authentication for sensitive actions]          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cancellation of certain visit types may require      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      additional verification                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Same-day cancellation has different policy than      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      cancellation a week out                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: verified patient_id, assurance_level]          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CONVERSATIONAL SLOT NEGOTIATION ───────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Extract scheduling parameters from the conversation]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Provider preference (named provider, specialty,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      established vs. new, language preference)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Location preference                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Visit type (mapped from natural language reason      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      for visit through institutional taxonomy)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-window preference (specific date, day of        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      week, time of day, urgency)                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Insurance plan (validated against the institution's  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      accepted-plans list for the proposed provider and    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      location)                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tool: slot_search]                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Given the parameters, query the scheduling system    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Return ranked candidate slots with provenance        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Apply the institution's ranking (preference for      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      established provider, preference for sooner,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      preference for previously-visited locations)         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Render candidate slots in plain English]               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Show 2-3 options, not 30                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Include the provider, the location, the time,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and any notable details (telehealth vs in-person,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      prep instructions for certain procedures)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Refinement loop]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient asks for variations ("anything earlier?",    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      "different day?", "different provider?")             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - LLM updates parameters and calls slot_search again   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Convergence when patient picks a slot or asks for    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      handoff                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [No-results handling]                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When slot_search returns nothing, the bot honestly   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      says so and offers alternatives:                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Wait-list enrollment                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Different provider                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Different location                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Different visit type (e.g., telehealth)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      - Handoff to live scheduler                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: chosen slot identifier]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── TRANSACTIONAL FULFILLMENT ─────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tool: slot_hold]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Place a short-term hold on the chosen slot           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Hold expires automatically (typical TTL: 5 minutes)  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Hold prevents concurrent booking from another        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      channel                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Confirmation prompt to the patient]                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Restate the proposed appointment                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      ("Tuesday May 28 at 7:30 AM with Dr. Patel at        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the Riverside Cardiology office")                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mention any pre-visit prep, parking, what to bring   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (drawn from the institution's knowledge base)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Ask for explicit confirmation                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Tool: slot_book]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Convert the hold to a confirmed appointment          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Triggers the institution's standard notification     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      workflow (confirmation text/email, calendar          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      attachment, pre-visit instructions)                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Returns the confirmation details                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Optional Tool: eligibility_check]                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Verifies insurance eligibility for the booked        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      appointment                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When the institution's policy is to verify at        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      booking time, this runs synchronously                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When the institution's policy is to verify in        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      batch later, this is skipped                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Failure handling]                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Slot no longer available -> graceful recovery,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      offer next alternatives                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Booking system error -> queue the request for        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      human follow-up, tell the patient honestly that      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      something went wrong                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Notification system error -> the appointment is      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      booked; the failed notification is queued for retry  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and surfaced in the operational dashboard            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: confirmation_id, appointment details, or       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    failure with disposition]                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── OUTPUT SAFETY SCREENING ───────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Same primitive as recipe 11.1]                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scope filter on generated response                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Vendor-managed guardrail layer                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Hallucination check (especially: did the bot         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      confirm an appointment that the booking tool         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      did not actually return?)                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: response cleared for delivery, or replaced     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    with a refusal-and-handoff]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND TELEMETRY ─────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances (scrubbed of inadvertent PHI)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated responses                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identity-verification outcome and assurance level    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Transactional outcomes (booked, rescheduled,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      canceled, failed, abandoned)                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Booking completion rate                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Median time to booking                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Handoff rate per intent and per failure mode         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identity-verification failure rate                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Slot-hold-but-not-confirmed rate                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool-call failure rate per tool                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      identity-verification path)                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled review queue]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of low-           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      confidence and escalated conversations               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers tag failure modes (wrong visit type,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      mis-ranked slots, identity-verification friction,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      booking error, etc.)                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals]      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the scheduling bot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **The tool surface is the bot's contract with the scheduling system.** The tools have versioned schemas. The schemas are owned jointly by the engineering team and the practice operations team. Changes to the tool surface (adding a parameter, changing the rank order in slot search, deprecating a tool) go through a documented change-management process. The bot's behavior is reproducible from the conversation log plus the active tool-surface version plus the active prompt and model versions. This is the load-bearing contract that makes the system safe to put in front of patients.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Identity verification is graduated by intent and channel.** A patient who is logged into the patient portal and asks to check their next appointment needs lower assurance than a patient who is in an unauthenticated web chat asking to cancel a same-day appointment. The bot's policy table maps (intent, channel, additional context) to required assurance level. The identity-verification tool can step the assurance up by asking for additional factors. The patient experience for high-assurance flows is intentionally a little more friction than for low-assurance flows, because the cost of a wrong action is higher.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Visit-type mapping is a managed asset.** The mapping from natural-language reasons for visit ("I need to follow up after my stress test") to institutional visit types ("cardiology established patient follow-up, 30 min") is a curated artifact owned by the practice operations team. The bot uses an LLM to do the mapping with the curated visit-type catalog as context, and the operations team reviews mis-mapped cases through the sampled review queue. The mapping evolves as the institution adds, retires, or restructures visit types.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Slot hold is the safety net for concurrency.** Without slot hold, two patients can race to book the same slot through different channels and one of them ends up double-booked. Slot hold with a TTL is the mechanism that prevents this. The bot's flow is always search-then-hold-then-confirm-then-book, never search-then-book. The TTL is short enough that abandoned holds release quickly (5 minutes is typical) and long enough that a patient deliberating over options has time to choose.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **The booking is durable; the conversation is not.** Once the appointment is booked, the source of truth is the scheduling system. The conversation log is the audit trail of how the booking happened, but the appointment itself lives in the scheduling system. The bot's job after booking is to confirm successfully and make sure the patient understands what was booked; the bot is not the appointment's home.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Compensation is a first-class operation.** When the bot books an appointment that turns out to be wrong (wrong visit type, wrong provider, wrong location, wrong time, wrong patient), the operational team needs to be able to undo and redo the booking cleanly. The architecture supports this with explicit "view this booking's history" and "compensate this booking" operations in the operational tooling. The audit trail for the original booking and the compensation is preserved together so that the institution can reproduce the full sequence of events for any patient complaint or any audit request.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **No-show and reminder workflows are integrations, not features.** The institution's existing reminder workflow (text reminders, phone-call reminders, email reminders) is a separate system. The booking tool triggers it as part of the standard booking flow. The cancellation tool similarly triggers the cancellation notification. The bot does not own these workflows; the bot's job is to integrate cleanly with them so that the patient's experience is consistent regardless of whether the appointment was booked through the bot, the call center, or the portal.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Scope filtering in the output checks for unauthorized actions.** The output safety screening from recipe 11.1 carries forward, with one new check: did the bot tell the patient an appointment was booked when the booking tool did not actually return success? This is a hallucination-style failure that has higher consequences in the scheduling context, because the patient may show up at an appointment that does not exist on the schedule. The output check verifies that any "your appointment is confirmed" claim in the response is supported by an actual successful booking-tool result.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Booking completion rates and identity-verification success rates can vary substantially by language, age cohort, channel, and (where available) other equity-relevant axes. The institution monitors these from launch and treats per-cohort disparity as a launch-gate criterion, not a post-launch dashboard.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
